Definition: The amount of medication taken per dose, as a quantity or range. Relative dose (e.g., per kg body weight or surface area) are indicated by specifying appropriate units (e.g., mg/kg or mg/m2 etc).

Short: SimpleQuantity or Range representing the amount of medication taken per dose, as a quantity or range. Relative dose (e.g., per kg body weight or surface area) are indicated by specifying appropriate units (e.g., mg/kg or mg/m2 etc).
